<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><head n="2.">Agro Climatic / Ecological Zones in the Uttar Pradesh:</head><p>The State of Uttar Pradesh is comprises 18 Divisions and 75 revenue districts. In order to derive maximum benefit from the available resources and prevailing growing conditions, an agro-climatic orientation is necessary in land use planning. Such an approach provides the desirable frame work of sustainable use of land, water and vegetation. The concept of zoning was mainly based on ecological land classification recognizing various components like soil, climate, topography, vegetation and crops etc. as major influencing factors. The zones were selected as contiguous areas within the State boundary and, to the extent possible, zones have homogenous physical characteristics such as topography, rainfall, soil, cropping pattern and availability of irrigation facilities. Uttar Pradesh, on the basis of rainfall, terrain and soil has been divided into 9 agro-climatic zones. State's agro-climatic zones are depicted as under:- </p></div><figure xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><head></head><label></label><figDesc></figDesc><graphic coords="2,98.74,322.04,284.57,288.17" type="bitmap" /></figure>
